# Determinism Envelope and Replay

## Must
- Run deterministic replay checks for simulation state-impacting changes.
- Use pinned replay environment for deterministic checks and emit environment fingerprint.
- Record RNG algorithm, seed, and stream partition policy in test artifacts.
- Keep stable ordering for state/event serialization and replay-critical reductions.
- Define acceptable platform variance budget explicitly for non-reference environments.

## Must Not
- Do not enable fast-math or nondeterministic execution modes in reference replay profile.
- Do not accept replay hash drift on canonical deterministic suite.

## Required Evidence
- Replay hash report (`D1`) and event stream consistency report (`D2`).
- Environment fingerprint artifact (compiler, OS/runtime, CPU/GPU class, key flags).
